<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="672" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[113,753,523,1027]" pageId="7" pageNumber="672">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,240,523,547]" pageId="7" pageNumber="672">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,233,523,547]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="672">Discussion</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
— This distinctive genus may be recognised by the strong anterior convergence of the eyes, with the minimum interocular distance being reached ventrally, beneath the apex of the head (
<figureCitation box="[304,393,619,643]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[836,871,2032,2054]" captionTargetBox="[841,1475,1144,1987]" captionTargetId="figure-620@6.[812,1478,1127,2022]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 16. Ctenipocoris asiaticus Montandon, female, dorsal habitus, specimen from Vietnam, Lam Dong Prov., nr. Lan Hanh, CL 3094 (Young Sohn illustration)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5352710" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5352710/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="672">Figs. 16</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[404,433,619,643]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="8.[834,878,1370,1392]" captionTargetBox="[839,1469,189,1335]" captionTargetId="figure-10@8.[825,1500,169,1344]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs. 17–20. Ctenipocoris asiaticus Montandon, structural details, specimen from Vietnam, Lam Dong Prov., nr. Lan Hanh, CL 3094. 17. Head, ventral view. 18. Male phallotheca. 19. Medial process of male phallotheca. 20. Male left paramere." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5352712" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5352712/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="672">17</figureCitation>
); the short legs set with stout, stubby spines (
<figureCitation box="[274,354,651,675]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[836,871,2032,2054]" captionTargetBox="[841,1475,1144,1987]" captionTargetId="figure-620@6.[812,1478,1127,2022]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 16. Ctenipocoris asiaticus Montandon, female, dorsal habitus, specimen from Vietnam, Lam Dong Prov., nr. Lan Hanh, CL 3094 (Young Sohn illustration)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5352710" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5352710/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="672">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
); the narrow, spine-like metaxyphus; and the maxillary plates with tufts of long setae arising from their margins and cradling the rostrum. The body is less strongly dorsoventrally flattened than in other members of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1876" box="[113,259,779,803]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="671" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Laccocorinae">Laccocorinae</taxonomicName>
, and the eyes as viewed from above are nearly triangular in shape (
<figureCitation box="[336,419,811,835]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[836,871,2032,2054]" captionTargetBox="[841,1475,1144,1987]" captionTargetId="figure-620@6.[812,1478,1127,2022]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 16. Ctenipocoris asiaticus Montandon, female, dorsal habitus, specimen from Vietnam, Lam Dong Prov., nr. Lan Hanh, CL 3094 (Young Sohn illustration)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5352710" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5352710/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="672">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
). The fore femur is small and stubby in relation to the tibia, being only weakly incrassate, and the apex of the foreleg bears two tarsal segments in both sexes, with two large apical claws. The male phallotheca is symmetrical (
<figureCitation box="[256,331,939,963]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="8.[834,878,1370,1392]" captionTargetBox="[839,1469,189,1335]" captionTargetId="figure-10@8.[825,1500,169,1344]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs. 17–20. Ctenipocoris asiaticus Montandon, structural details, specimen from Vietnam, Lam Dong Prov., nr. Lan Hanh, CL 3094. 17. Head, ventral view. 18. Male phallotheca. 19. Medial process of male phallotheca. 20. Male left paramere." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5352712" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5352712/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="672">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
), unlike the asymmetrical character state exhibited in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1876" box="[250,367,972,995]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Heleocoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="672" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[250,367,972,995]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="672">Heleocoris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1856" box="[422,541,972,995]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Laccocoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="672" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[422,541,972,995]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="672">Laccocoris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the parameres are elongate and unmodified (
<figureCitation box="[436,569,1003,1027]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="8.[834,878,1370,1392]" captionTargetBox="[839,1469,189,1335]" captionTargetId="figure-10@8.[825,1500,169,1344]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs. 17–20. Ctenipocoris asiaticus Montandon, structural details, specimen from Vietnam, Lam Dong Prov., nr. Lan Hanh, CL 3094. 17. Head, ventral view. 18. Male phallotheca. 19. Medial process of male phallotheca. 20. Male left paramere." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5352712" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5352712/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="672">Figs. 18, 20</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[113,752,1067,1347]" pageId="7" pageNumber="672">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Montandon" authorityYear="1897" box="[113,251,1068,1091]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Ctenipocoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="672" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[113,251,1068,1091]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="672">Ctenipocoris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was formerly considered to be an exclusively Paleotropical genus, but various Neotropical species previously held in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1876" box="[324,442,1132,1155]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Heleocoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="672" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[324,442,1132,1155]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="672">Heleocoris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have now been re-assigned to it (D. 
<bibRefCitation author="Polhemus, D" box="[207,383,1163,1187]" pageId="7" pageNumber="672" pagination="370" refId="ref18886" refString="Polhemus, D. A., 1987. Heleocoris brasiliensis De Carlo is a Ctenipocoris (Hemiptera: Naucoridae). Pan-Pacific Entomologist, 63: 370." type="journal article" year="1987">Polhemus, 1987</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lopez Ruf, M" box="[396,582,1163,1187]" pageId="7" pageNumber="672" pagination="19 - 24" refId="ref18506" refString="Lopez Ruf, M., 2004. Redescription de Ctenipocoris schadei y descripcion de las larvas III y V (Hemiptera: Naucoridae). Revista de la Sociedad Entomologia Argentina, 63 (3 - 4): 19 - 24." type="journal article" year="2004">López Ruf, 2004</bibRefCitation>
; J. Polhemus &amp; D. Polhemus, 2008). In Asia the genus is represented by a widespread species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Montandon" authorityYear="1897" box="[331,457,1227,1251]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Ctenipocoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="672" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asiaticus">
<emphasis box="[331,349,1228,1251]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="672">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[362,457,1228,1251]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="672">asiaticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which occurs in 
<collectingCountry box="[644,752,1227,1251]" name="Singapore" pageId="7" pageNumber="672">Singapore</collectingCountry>
and Peninsular 
<collectingCountry box="[280,381,1259,1283]" name="Malaysia" pageId="7" pageNumber="672">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
. A second species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zettel" authorityYear="2012" box="[590,696,1260,1283]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Ctenipocoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="672" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinicus">
<emphasis box="[590,696,1260,1283]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="672">C. sinicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, was recently described from 
<collectingCountry box="[392,457,1291,1315]" name="China" pageId="7" pageNumber="672">China</collectingCountry>
based on a single female specimen (
<bibRefCitation author="Zettel, H" box="[229,366,1323,1347]" pageId="7" pageNumber="672" pagination="27 - 36" refId="ref20225" refString="Zettel, H., 2012. New creeping water bugs (Insecta: Heteroptera: Naucoridae) from China and the Philippines. Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien, Serie B, 113: 27 - 36." type="journal article" year="2012">Zettel, 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
